class vizasm.model.asm.ivar.IVar.IVar(ivar_class, ivar_ref=None)[source]¶

Bases: object, vizasm.model.objc.object.nsobject.NSObjectInterface.NSObjectInterface, vizasm.model.objc.function.MsgSendInterface.MsgSendInterface

Represents an ivar (instance variable) e.g. created out of this asmline: “[ds:_OBJC_IVAR_$_AppDelegate.obj3]”

where obj3 is the variable of the ObjcClass AppDelegate

which points to a MsgSend like [[Object3 alloc] init]

Parameters:

__ivar_class: ObjcClass :

ObjcClass e.g. created from “[ds:_OBJC_IVAR_$_AppDelegate.obj3]”

__ivar_ref: MsgSend, optional (default is None) :

the MsgSend where the ivar points to

Methods

create_ivar_lookup_entry(ivar_ref_lookup) Create a lookup entry in the IVarLookup using ivar_class as key and ivar_ref as value.
create_msg_send(selector[, ivar_ref_lookup]) Create a MsgSend with the specified selector.

create_ivar_lookup_entry(ivar_ref_lookup)[source]¶

Create a lookup entry in the IVarLookup using ivar_class as key and ivar_ref as value. If ivar_ref is None, no entry will be created.

Parameters:

ivar_ref_lookup: IVarRefLookup :

the class where the ivar_ref will be stored
Returns:

True :

if the entry could be created

False :

if the entry could not be created because the ivar_ref was not available
create_msg_send(selector, ivar_ref_lookup=None, *args, **kwargs)[source]¶

Create a MsgSend with the specified selector. If the ivar_ref is not None, this will be used for the MsgSend. Otherwise the ivar_class is used.

Parameters:

selector: Selector :

the Selector with which the MsgSend shall be created.

ivar_ref_lookup: IVarRefLookup, optional :

if given, the ivar_ref will be resolved

Returns :

——- :

MsgSend :

the created MsgSend with ivar_ref or ivar_class
get_ivar_class()[source]¶
get_ivar_ref()[source]¶

Get the ivar_ref. You might want to call resolve_ivar_ref() before to resolve it.

get_nsobject()[source]¶
ivar_class¶

__ivar_class(ObjcClass) – ObjcClass e.g. create from “[ds:_OBJC_IVAR_$_AppDelegate.obj3]”

ivar_ref¶

__ivar_ref(MsgSend) – the MsgSend where the ivar points to

resolve_ivar_ref(ivar_ref_lookup)[source]¶

Resolve the ivar_ref from ivar_ref_look and set it. The value can be obtained via get_ivar_ref() if no exception occurred.

Parameters:

ivar_ref_lookup: IVarRefLookup :

the class where the ivar_ref is stored
Raises:

IvarRefWrongTypeException :

if the ivar_ref could not be resolved to the correct type (should be MsgSend)

IvarRefCouldNotBeResolvedException :

if the ivar_ref could not be resolved at all
